Forked from RustQC
------------------

liquidqc is a hard fork of RustQC, originally developed by Seqera Labs:

  https://github.com/seqeralabs/RustQC

RustQC is copyright (c) Seqera Labs and contributors, licensed under
GPL-3.0-or-later. The full upstream history is preserved in this
repository's git log; the `upstream` git remote points at the original
project so improvements can be cherry-picked in either direction.

Inherited from RustQC, liquidqc reimplements (and continues to credit)
the following upstream tools, each with its own license and citation:

  - dupRadar (Sayols et al., 2016) — BMC Bioinformatics 17:428
  - featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014) — Bioinformatics 30(7):923-930
  - RSeQC (Wang et al., 2012) — Bioinformatics 28(16):2184-2185
  - preseq (Daley & Smith, 2013) — Nature Methods 10(4):325-327
  - samtools (Li et al., 2009) — Bioinformatics 25(16):2078-2079
  - Qualimap (Okonechnikov et al., 2016) — Bioinformatics 32(2):292-294

When liquidqc emits results, the included `CITATIONS.md` file lists
the specific tools used in that run with full bibliographic citations.

Liquidqc-specific additions (Phase 1+) extend the inherited base with
cfRNA-focused fragmentomics features. These additions remain
GPL-3.0-or-later as required by the upstream license.
